            <pb facs="https://leaf.bucknell.edu/sites/default/files/2026-01/diary31.jpg"/>
            <head>Friday 31st</head>
            <p>The wind blew pretty hard all day, and this evening set in with storm and rain.
               This morning we saw a little schooner standing in toward us, running hard before
               the stiff nor-wester, steered like a hog, the sailors said, badley steered. One of
               our gun boats ran out to her, she dropped sail and was towed in. it had on board 2
               New Yorkers, 1 New Jersey man &amp; one N. Carolinian - they had been impressed
               into a company. answered roll call last night, stationed at Middleton, Hyde
               County, just across the sound, &amp; came in this morning. There were 800
               stationed there - they said it was reported that there were ten thousand at
               Roanoke Island and that we had 30,000 We received our mail this afternoon about a
               bushel &amp; a half. I rec'd 3 letters from John &amp; Annie of the 7.14. 20.
               January.</p>
